<subSubSection id="AFF7A09A2520FFFF8AA2FE1EFC0D1859" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="E752F3112520FFFF8AA2FE1EFC0D1859" blockId="65.[667,1193,212,1377]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
HOST ASSOCIATIONS: All 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BEAFE19FD6D1AF6" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8BEAFE19FBD81AD5" box="[1008,1136,388,411]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are associated with 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BA4FE3FFB841AF6" box="[958,1068,418,440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B03FE22FBC61A9B" authority="(Schuh, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Schuh" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[793,1134,447,470]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Psorothamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B03FE22FC131A98" box="[793,955,447,470]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Psorothamnus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8BD4FE22FBCD1A9B" author="Schuh, R. T." box="[974,1125,447,469]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="159 - 166" refId="ref129356" refString="Schuh, R. T. 1989. Review of Daleapidea Knight (Heteroptera: Miridae: Orthotylinae: Orthotylini). Journal of the New York Entomological Society 97 (2): 159 - 166." type="journal article" year="1989">Schuh, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8C67FE5DFD501ABD" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8C67FE5DFD501ABD" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was named by 
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8BABFE41FBFE1ABC" author="Knight, H. H." box="[945,1110,476,498]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 282" refId="ref128169" refString="Knight, H. H. 1968. Taxonomic review: Miridae of the Nevada test site and the western United States. Brigham Young University Science Bulletin Biological Series 9 (3): 1 - 282." type="journal article" year="1968">Knight (1968)</bibRefCitation>
due to its association with ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BBAFE64FC4B195E" box="[928,995,505,528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8BBAFE64FC4B195E" box="[928,995,505,528]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Dalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’’ plants and by the apparent resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BE5FD8BFBF31963" baseAuthorityName="Carvalho" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1023,1115,534,557]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Lopidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8BE5FD8BFBF31963" box="[1023,1115,534,557]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Lopidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8C67FD85FD141905" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8C67FD85FD141905" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Dalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’’ species associated with 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BFCFDA9FBCE1905" box="[998,1126,564,587]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8BFCFDA9FBCE1905" box="[998,1126,564,587]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned by Knight are now all segregated in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B15FDF3FBDB19CB" authority="(Barneby, 1977)" baseAuthorityName="Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[783,1139,622,645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Psorothamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B15FDF3FC1919CB" box="[783,945,622,645]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Psorothamnus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8BA5FDF2FBC319CB" author="Barneby, R. C." box="[959,1131,623,645]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 891" refId="ref125763" refString="Barneby, R. C. 1977. Daleae imagines: an illustrat- ed revision of Errazuriza Philippi, Psorothamnus Rydberg, Marina Leibmann, and Dalea Lucanus emend. Barneby, including all species of Leguminosae tribe Amorpheae Borissova ever referred to Dalea. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 27: 1 - 891." type="journal article" year="1977">Barneby, 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Old labels mentioning ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B88FD16FC7E19EC" box="[914,982,651,674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B88FD16FC7E19EC" box="[914,982,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Dalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’’ as host plants cannot unambiguously be identified and may be any of the segregated genera, or one of the more than 160 described species of 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8C7FFD7EFB0119B4" box="[1125,1193,739,762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8C7FFD7EFB0119B4" box="[1125,1193,739,762]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Dalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8AB9FC9CFCF81858" author="Barneby, R. C." box="[675,848,769,791]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 891" refId="ref125763" refString="Barneby, R. C. 1977. Daleae imagines: an illustrat- ed revision of Errazuriza Philippi, Psorothamnus Rydberg, Marina Leibmann, and Dalea Lucanus emend. Barneby, including all species of Leguminosae tribe Amorpheae Borissova ever referred to Dalea. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 27: 1 - 891." type="journal article" year="1977">Barneby, 1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8B47FC9CFC301859" author="Barneby, R. C." box="[861,920,769,791]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref125821" refString="Barneby, R. C. 1990. Two new taxa in Dalea (Fabaceae: Amorpheae) from southern Mexico and northern Chile. Brittonia 42 (2): 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="1990">1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AFF7A09A2520FFFF8AA2FC80FCC81E2F" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E752F3112520FFFF8AA2FC80FB011F4F" blockId="65.[667,1193,212,1377]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
DISCUSSION: 
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8B42FC83FC5D187B" author="Schuh, R. T." box="[856,1013,798,821]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="159 - 166" refId="ref129356" refString="Schuh, R. T. 1989. Review of Daleapidea Knight (Heteroptera: Miridae: Orthotylinae: Orthotylini). Journal of the New York Entomological Society 97 (2): 159 - 166." type="journal article" year="1989">Schuh (1989)</bibRefCitation>
in his revision of 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8AA4FCA6FC96181C" box="[702,830,827,850]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8AA4FCA6FC96181C" box="[702,830,827,850]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
documented for the first time the distinctive structure present in the fore tibia. This distal flattened area on the ventral surface of the fore tibia has a set of setae on its lateral margins that vary with respect to their density. 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B23FC50FB8118AA" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1918" box="[825,1065,973,996]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B23FC50FB8118AA" box="[825,1065,973,996]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea albescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species in which the setae are not densely set.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E752F3112520FFFF8AA2FB94FCC81E2F" blockId="65.[667,1193,212,1377]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation id="837C8EE02520FFFF8AA2FB94FCE31F50" author="Schuh, R. T." box="[696,843,1033,1055]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="159 - 166" refId="ref129356" refString="Schuh, R. T. 1989. Review of Daleapidea Knight (Heteroptera: Miridae: Orthotylinae: Orthotylini). Journal of the New York Entomological Society 97 (2): 159 - 166." type="journal article" year="1989">Schuh (1989</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5L) presented a schematic illustration for the phallotheca of 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8C96FBBAFD551F14" authorityName="Uhler" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hadronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8C96FBBAFD551F14" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">D. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This structure was misinterpreted in the provided drawing as being completely open dorsally with overlapping lateral margins. Nevertheless, the phallotheca of the three described species of 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8BD7FB25FBE51F81" box="[973,1101,1208,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Daleapidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8BD7FB25FBE51F81" box="[973,1101,1208,1231]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Daleapidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a particular configuration (fig. 21), similar to the 
<typeStatus id="38564DB32520FFFF8AC8FB6EFCAC1E46" box="[722,772,1267,1288]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
found in 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B82FB6FFB9A1E47" authorityName="Forero" authorityYear="2008" box="[920,1074,1266,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Aoplonemella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B82FB6FFB9A1E47" box="[920,1074,1266,1289]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Aoplonemella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 17), 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8A81FA8DFCB11E6B" authorityName="Forero" authorityYear="2008" box="[667,793,1296,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Origonema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8A81FA8DFCB11E6B" box="[667,793,1296,1317]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Origonema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 43), and particularly to the form found in 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8B59FAB1FC611E0D" box="[835,969,1324,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hadronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8B59FAB1FC611E0D" box="[835,969,1324,1347]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Hadronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20ED88922520FFFF8C18FAB1FB011E0D" box="[1026,1193,1324,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hadronemidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5992F032520FFFF8C18FAB1FB011E0D" box="[1026,1193,1324,1347]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Hadronemidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(figs. 28, 29, 39).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
